In this statement, the President acknowledges the start of Hanukkah and highlights the significance of the holiday. He emphasizes that Hanukkah represents the fight for justice in the face of adversity and the triumph of liberty over tyranny. The President encourages reflection on the rejection of persecution and the miracles that can occur during difficult times. He also calls for Americans to renew their commitment to advocating for the dignity of every human being. The President concludes by wishing everyone a happy Hanukkah and expressing his hope that the lights of the menorah bring warmth and joy to their homes.